{"lemma":"صُدْغُ","slug":"صُدْغُ","root":"ص.د.غ","root_slug":"ص-د-غ","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-د-غ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23971","n23972","n23973"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%92%D8%BA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"temple"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṣdġ. Compare Hebrew צֶדַע (ṣéḏaʿ) and Classical Syriac ܨܕܥܐ (sˤɛðʕɑ, “temple, jaw”)."},"ipa":["/sˤadɣ/","/sˤudɣ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23971","headword_ar":"صُدْغٌ","root":"Sdg","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temple;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part between the eye and the ear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part between the outer angle of the eye and the root"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the ear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the head that slopes down to the place of attachment of the jaws;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expl. by AZ, it is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of juncture between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lHyp","text_ar":"لحية"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHoY","text_ar":"لَحْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jaw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with the explanation next preceding,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the main portion of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the head, to the part beneath the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaron","text_ar":"قَرْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temporal ridge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of what are termed the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SudogaAni","text_ar":"صُدْغَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, A, TA:) ISd mentions also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sudug","text_ar":"صُدُغ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as occurring in poetry, and expresses a doubt whether it be, or be not, peculiar to poetry: (TA:) and sometimes they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sudogN","text_ar":"سُدْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":": Ktr says that certain persons of the Benoo-Temeem, called Bel'ambar [a contraction of Benu-l-'Ambar], change"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or use these two letters indiscriminately] when followed by any of the letters"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"g","text_ar":"غ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x","text_ar":"خ"},{"kind":"text","text":", whether the latter be second or third or fourth; saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siraATN","text_ar":"سِرَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiraATN","text_ar":"صِرَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basoTapN","text_ar":"بَسْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baSoTapN","text_ar":"بَصْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayoqalN","text_ar":"سَيْقَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayoqalN","text_ar":"صَيْقَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.: (S, O:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSodaAgN","text_ar":"اَصْدَاغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, TA, [in all except the Msb mentioned after the signification expl. in the next sentence, and properly a pl. of pauc.,]) and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSodugN","text_ar":"اَصْدُغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is probably used only as a pl. of pauc.]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair that hangs down upon the place above-mentioned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SudogN","text_ar":"صُدْغٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaqorabN","text_ar":"مُعَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A curled lock of hair hanging down upon the temple"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AZ","A","TA","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n23972","headword_ar":"صَدَغٌ","root":"Sdg","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Crookedness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclining."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See 1, near the end.])"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n23973","headword_ar":"صُدُغٌ","root":"Sdg","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SudogN","text_ar":"صُدْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}